FBIS3-49548 "dreeu008_c_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 CZECH REPUBLIC EBRD Approves Loans for Vehicle Firm, TV Network LD1101174194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1500 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101174194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] The management of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development [EBRD] has approved a capital investment of 6.7 million ECU's for Karosa Vysoke Myto [East Bohemian coach manufacturer, which signed a joint-venture agreement with Renault Vehicules Industries in November 1993]. The EBRD management also approved a 15-million-ECU loan and the possible underwriting of a loan of the same size from Czech banks. The EBRD also approved a $20-million loan, which, if necessary, could be used as a guarantee for the joint-stock company Kabelnet's project to install a 12-channel cable television network in the south city in Prague and in Tabor
